so core_initcall(), but it should be linked <br />later. And module loading will happen later. mm/page_alloc.c has special <br />code for bootup, and intel-rng.c should be a normal driver.<br /><br />So it _should_ be ok. But I really didn't test. And my default kernel <br />config doesn't even have CONFIG_STOP_MACHINE enabled, so I'm not the best <br />person to test. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
